article.description: Wofford defeats UNC-Greensboro 70-52 to open tourney defense
article.headline: Wofford defeats UNC-Greensboro 70-52 to open tourney defense
article.linkText: Wofford defeats UNC-Greensboro 70-52 to open tourney defense
article.story: ASHEVILLE, N.C. -- Spencer Collins poured in 21 points -- and all five starters scored at least eight -- as top-seeded, defending champion Wofford made half its field goals to throttle No. 8 seed UNC-Greensboro 70-52 in the Southern Conference tournament quarterfinals on Saturday. The Terriers (26-6) meet fourth-seeded Western Carolina in Sunday's semifinals. Wofford is seeking a fourth SoCon tourney championship in six seasons. Collins made 9 of 14 field goals and scored more than 20 points for the second time in Wofford's last three games. Collins had a career-high 26 against Mercer on Feb. 26. He nailed a 3-pointer Saturday to help kick off an 18-4 run as the Terriers broke away early, en route to a 30-20 halftime lead. Lee Skinner and Karl Cochran scored 12 points each, Justin Gordon 10 and Eric Garcia eight for Wofford. Kayel Locke scored 17 with 10 rebounds to lead UNC-Greensboro (11-22) and Diante Baldwin added 13 points.
